<h2>Help</h2>
<p> <a class="brand" href="<%= root_url%>"> grave.io </a> is just another
paste bin implementation aimed for inhouse use. </p>

<h3>How to use</h3>
<ul>
  <li><b>New snippet</b></li>
  Create a new snippet that needs to be published. Fill out title
  and content and press to create. You will be redirected to your new
  entry, where you easy get a short url to this snippet.
  <li><b>Destroy snippet</b></li>
  Click on the trash icon below of a snippet and confirm it.
</ul>
<h3>Command line interface</h3>
<ul>
  For easier posting of content to graveio, you can use bury, a ruby command
  line tool which also integrates to vim.
  <br \>
  To integrate it in vim simply add this line to your .vimrc:
  <pre class="help">map &lt;F2&gt; :w !bury -t %&lt;CR&gt;</pre>
  The default host and port for the tool can be configured via a rc file
  located at "~/.buryrc"
  <br \>
  Example configuration:
  <pre class="help">
default:
  :host: 172.30.200.153
  :port: 3000</pre>
</ul>

